The U.S. Government has issued a statement deploring the murder of Xulhaz Mannan in Dhaka, Bangladesh. Mannan, an employee of the U.S. Agency for International Development, worked at the U.S. Embassy in Dhaka and advocated for justice, equality, and human rights for all. The U.S. Government expresses its condolences to Mannan's loved ones and urges the Government of Bangladesh to bring the perpetrators of this crime to justice.